Date: Tue 14 Oct 2014
Source: Global Post, Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/xinhua-news-agency/141014/vietnam-reports-anthrax-northern-locality


Viet Nam reports anthrax in northern locality
---------------------------------------------
Viet Nam's northern Ha Giang province, some 320 km [about 200 mi due] north of the capital Hanoi, reported 9 cases of anthrax in humans related to consumption of meat from dead livestock.

During [17 Sep to 9 Oct 2014], medical centers in Meo Vac District in Ha Giang reported 9 cases with clinical presentation of cutaneous anthrax. No fatality was record so far, according to Viet Nam's state-run news agency VNA on [Tue 14 Oct 2014]. Among the 9 cases, there are 4 men aged between 24 and 30, and 5 children, reported VNA.

The medical agencies of Ha Giang have implemented preventive measures and sent samples to the National Institute of Hygiene and Epidemiology for diagnosis.

Anthrax is a disease caused by bacteria [_Bacillus anthracis_]. Cutaneous anthrax presents a boil-like skin lesion that eventually forms an ulcer with a black center.

