[Anthrax has long been a chronic problem in the northern provinces of Viet Nam. To find Ha Giang, on the border with China>, go to http://www.onlineasiatravel.com/images/vn/vietnam-map.png. It is a mountainous province with narrow valleys (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C3%A0_Giang_Province). Meo Vac district is remote but enjoys a Sunday cattle market (see http://vietnamhagiang.com/).

While outbreaks of anthrax in northern Viet Nam are sporadic, they can sometimes get out of hand as vaccination has ceased to be a routine. And this is accompanied by multiple human cases, such as 52+ in Dien Bien Province in 2011, and 13 cases with 2 deaths in Ha Giang in 2008. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2866627,1151.]
